Key Match Events: Jake Bauers hit an RBI single in the ninth inning to score Jackson Chourio, winning the game 2-1.
Pre-Game Insights: The Milwaukee Brewers had clinched the NL Central earlier when the Cubs lost, but needed to win this game to prevent the Phillies from securing a playoff berth.
Post-Match Reflections: Aaron Nola stated that the Brewers are a grinding team and they executed their pitches well.
Jake Bauers said the vibe in the clubhouse was focused on winning the game despite clinching the division.
Willy Adames said the team proved doubters wrong and hopes to win it all.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Milwaukee's Freddy Peralta allowed one run on two hits in five innings, striking out nine and walking two.
Philadelphia's Aaron Nola went seven innings, allowing one run on three hits while striking out nine and walking one.
